111827;border-bottom:1px solid #1f2937;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 20px;\">\n    <div style=\"color:#9ca3af;font-family:monospace;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;margin-bottom:8px;\">🔄 Rotation</div>\n    <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#9ca3af;\">No rotation suggested today. VERA stop ($38) is not threatened. The CELC play is a new cash deployment, not a rotation from VERA — thesis for holding VERA (ORIGIN 3 Q3) is independent of the CELC binary. Holding both positions is the correct structure.</div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table>\n\n<!-- IBKR INTELLIGENCE — UNAVAILABLE -->\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background:#0a0f1a;border-bottom:1px solid #1f2937;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:12px 20px;\">\n    <div style=\"padding:10px 14px;background:#0f172a;border-left:3px solid #374151;border-radius:4px;font-size:12px;color:#6b7280;\">\n      📊 <strong>IBKR Intelligence</strong> — Section unavailable. IBKR connector did not respond. Performance (MTD/YTD TWR), allocation breakdown, and position themes skipped. This section will auto-populate when IBKR connector is restored.\n    </div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table>\n\n<!-- EDUCATION — CONCEPT #4 -->\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background:#0f172a;border-bottom:1px solid #1f2937;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:16px 20px;\">\n    <div style=\"background:#1e1b4b;border-left:4px solid #6366f1;border-radius:6px;padding:16px;\">\n      <div style=\"color:#818cf8;font-family:monospace;font-size:11px;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.08em;margin-bottom:8px;\">📚 Concept #4 — Price/Book (P/B)</div>\n      <div style=\"color:#e5e7eb;font-size:13px;line-height:1.7;\">\n        <p style=\"margin:0 0 10px;\">P/B = market cap ÷ book value (assets minus liabilities). Historically useful when companies <em>were</em> their balance sheets — factories, inventory, machinery, where liquidation value approximated real worth. Modern businesses have broken this entirely. <strong>VERA's book value</strong> is mostly cash from equity raises and some lab equipment. The actual asset — atacicept, the TRUTAKNA IP, the ORIGIN 3 clinical data rights — has no balance sheet entry. The drug itself doesn't appear until it generates revenue. So VERA might trade at 30–50x book, and that multiple tells you nothing useful. The real value is a probability-weighted future cash flow from a drug that just got accelerated approval. P/B can't capture that.</p>\n        <p style=\"margin:0;\">Where P/B <em>does</em> work: banks, REITs, industrials — capital-structure businesses where the balance sheet <em>is</em> the business. A bank's book value is what it actually lends and earns on. Check P/B for those. For every tech and biotech name you hold: ignore it entirely. The multiple will always look \"expensive\" — that's not a signal, it's just the wrong frame.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-top:10px;color:#6366f1;font-size:12px;\"><strong>Also today:</strong> <em>Tangible book value</em> — book value minus goodwill and intangibles. Even stricter, even less applicable to VERA or any drug IP play.</div>\n    </div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table>\n\n<!-- FOOTER -->\n<table width=\"100%\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" style=\"background:#0a0f1a;border-top:1px solid #1f2937;\">\n  <tr><td style=\"padding:14px 20px;\">\n    <div style=\"color:#374151;font-size:10px;line-height:1.6;\">\n      This is research, not financial advice. Verify all prices in your IBKR account before executing any trade. IBKR connector was unavailable — all position prices sourced from web search (web search timestamp: approximately market close July 13–14, 2026). VERA price discrepancy: web search ~$42.45, portfolio.json IBKR note $40.70 — verify the actual close in your app.<br><br>\n      Daily Portfolio Check · Abbas Al Madani · Kuwait (UTC+3) · Prices: web search (IBKR unavailable) · Education: Concept #4 Price/Book (P/B)<br>\n      abbashm9/portfolio-skills · portfolio.json last_updated: 2026-07-14T00:00:00+03:00\n    </div>\n  </td></tr>\n</table>\n"
